Thunor: I've fixed these or found them to have already been fixed:
------------------------------------------------------------------
(1)  05.02-combo_input: the input is not working in comboboxes.
(2)  There is no gtk_combo_box support, we have only gtk_combo.
(3)  The edit is not producing value on the output.
(4)  06.01-editor_attributes: The edit does not handle the <default> attribute.
(5)  06.01-editor_attributes: Custom type properties, such as 
      "wrap-mode"            GtkWrapMode           : Read / Write
     are not supported. (Thunor: it already works as a tag attribute).
(6)  10.01-vbox_and_hbox_attributes: we always packing with the defaults.
(7)  Segfault if no name given for the frame.
(8)  All the action handling functions (button_pressed) should get a type
     parameter showing what kind of command has to be executed.
(10) The tree widget is virtually unhandled.
(12) Segmentation fault when the table has no variable name.
(13) Unpaired " in variable output broke shell eval. Fixed by escaping
     double quotes and backslashes in print_variables().
     See examples/entry/entry_quote_in_value and its test
     tests/ft_entry_quote_in_value/ft_entry_quote_in_value.py.

Thunor: These still remain:
---------------------------
(9)  Opening multiple window with the same name leads to confusion.
(11) At the creation of the widgets the initialization should be sorted
     as the dependencies are dictating.
(14) The <text wrap="true" width-chars="40"> label is not wrapping long text.
     See examples/languages/bash_script_event_driven and its test
     tests/ft_bash_script_event_driven/ft_bash_script_event_driven.py.
(15) The launch action uses nested gtk_main() loops which breaks AT-SPI
     accessibility for secondary windows. The nested loop design is
     required because the program uses exit() to terminate. Refactoring
     to use gtk_main_quit() and a single main loop would fix AT-SPI and
     allow proper automated testing of multi-window examples.
     See examples/languages/bash_script_multi_window.

Unsupported GTK3 widgets:
-------------------------
(16) Add GtkDialog support (base dialog with standard button area).
(17) Add GtkAboutDialog support (application info and credits).
(18) Add GtkFileChooserDialog support (file open/save picker).
(19) Add GtkColorChooserDialog support (color picker dialog).
(20) Add GtkFontChooserDialog support (font picker dialog).
(21) Add GtkMessageDialog support (alerts and confirmations).
(22) Add GtkAssistant support (multi-step wizard).
(23) Add GtkGrid support (flexible row/column grid layout).
(24) Add GtkFixed support (pixel-positioned children).
(25) Add GtkFlowBox support (reflowing wrap layout).
(26) Add GtkHeaderBar support (CSD header with title and buttons).
(27) Add GtkStack and GtkStackSwitcher support (one-visible-child with switcher).
(28) Add GtkPaned support (resizable split pane).
(29) Add GtkOverlay support (layered widget stacking).
(30) Add GtkRevealer support (animated show/hide).
(31) Add GtkInfoBar support (in-window notification bar).
(32) Add GtkButtonBox support (specialized button container).
(33) Add GtkPopover support (popup attached to a widget).
(34) Add GtkSearchEntry support (entry with search icon/clearing).
(35) Add GtkSwitch support (on/off toggle).
(36) Add GtkCalendar support (date picker).
(37) Add GtkScaleButton and GtkVolumeButton support (button with popup slider).
(38) Add GtkImage support (general image display, replacing limited pixmap).
(39) Add GtkDrawingArea support (custom Cairo drawing canvas).
(40) Add GtkGLArea support (OpenGL rendering).
(41) Add GtkSpinner support (animated activity indicator).
(42) Add GtkLevelBar support (segmented level/progress indicator).
(43) Add GtkAccelLabel support (label showing keyboard shortcuts).
(44) Add GtkLinkButton support (clickable URL).
(45) Add GtkListBox support (vertical list with arbitrary row widgets).
(46) Add GtkIconView support (icon grid from TreeModel).
(47) Add GtkToolbar support (toolbar container).
(48) Add GtkToolButton, GtkToggleToolButton, GtkRadioToolButton support.
(49) Add GtkMenuButton support (button with attached menu/popover).
(50) Add GtkApplicationWindow support (app window with GAction integration).
(51) Add GtkShortcutsWindow support (keyboard shortcuts overlay).
(52) Pango <span> attributes containing double quotes break inside quoted labels
     because the lexer treats the inner quotes as string terminators.
(53) Text widget auto-sizes width-chars to the longest line in the label,
     but this can make windows too wide. Consider capping or improving the
     heuristic for better default geometry.
